cmg.cnsim.engine.transaction

Class TransactionGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • cmg.cnsim.engine.transaction.TransactionGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITxContainer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Block, TransactionWorkload

    public class TransactionGroup
extends java.lang.Object
implements ITxContainer
    A list containing various transactions. Can be used as a block or other needed grouping (e.g. pool).
    Author:
    Sotirios Liaskos for the Conceptual Modeling Group @ York University

      • TransactionGroup

        public TransactionGroup(java.lang.String fileName,
                        boolean hasHeader)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Loads a transaction group from a text file. Each line in the file is a separate transaction. Each transaction is a comma separated string containing the following information: Transaction ID, Time Created, Total Value, Total Size, First Arrival NodeID. Transaction ID must run from 1 to n strictly increasing by 1 at each step (error otherwise). Time must not decrease as transactions IDs increase.
        Parameters:
        fileName - A name to the text file containing the transactions.
        hasHeader - Whether the file has a header.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Formatting error.

      • getTopN

        public TransactionGroup getTopN(float sizeLimit,
                                java.util.Comparator<Transaction> comp)
        Retrieves a TransactionGroup containing the top N transactions based on a given size limit and comparator.
        Parameters:
        sizeLimit - The maximum cumulative size in bytes of transactions allowed in the the result.
        comp - The comparator used to sort the transactions.
        Returns:
        A TransactionGroup object containing the top N transactions that do not exceed sizeLimit based on given comparator.
